<Content>Relaxing My husband and I just returned from a week in Vieques. We were looking for a quiet place with beautiful beaches and this is what we got. We stayed at the Martineau Bay Resort and Spa. Our room was very large. The Resort was somewhat worn but not in any way unacceptable. It was also empty! It felt as if we had the place to ourselves. We ate dinner in the hotel one night. It is called Paso Fino and it was delicious! We ate at Uva, El Quenepo, Bananas, Duffy's and the Trade Winds. Our favorite breakfast spot was Belly Buttons. The banana pancakes were scrumptious. The bananas come from the owners backyard and are known as apple-bananas. YUM! We really enjoyed meeting the owners. Roy's coffee house was also a great spot for breakfast as well as take out lunch food.It is so important to have your own car while on the island. The beaches are beautiful. Blue Beach was our favorite!We booked a tour with Abe's kayaks to go to the Bio Luminescent Bay. It was a wonderful experience that you simply must do if you are going to Vieques. Abe was a great tour guide! One should definitely consider kayaking versus taking a noisy, bay-polluting boat out into the bay. You will not be disappointed! 
