<Author>waverunr
<Content>march 14th trip just returned from Vieques. Beautiful island; unspoiled. We took the ferry from fajardo to Vieques. ($4 round trip). The navy runs the ferry, but if you are going on a holiday or weekend get there about 1 1/2 hrs before it leaves. It gets very crowded. First come basis. Sat in the back outside, beautiful views. On the way back we took the 6:30 am and had roosters crowing on board. It takes about 1 1/2 hrs, not bad for price. We had a driver take us to the ferry from San Juan and pick us back up on return. I reserved her in advance. Her web site is [--]. She charged 65 each way for our family of 4. She was always there waiting for us-so no hunting for transportation. On Vieques we took a cab to the hotel about $12. We stayed At Martineau Bay Resort. Very nice, large room overlooking the ocean and pool. Huge bathroom, large sunken tub, walk in shower, double bowl sinks. We ate dinner and lunch by the pool grill, pizza $12, hamburgers $12 food was good and it was nice to eat outside.They have 2 beaches, one is a bit rocky and the other has some waves good for boogey boarding. They were never crowded, the most was about 8 people. The resort is beautiful and the views walking around our spectacular. We rented a car from Martineau Rental. They pick you up at the hotel and bring you back. Drove around the island and checked out other beaches. Rented snorkel equipment in town, $15 per person a day. Drove to Green Beach, snorkeling was good, but stay away from the point -current is strong there. we saw schools of fish, sting rays, barracudas, and even an octopus. Had the whole beach to ourselves. The best thing to do is to see the bioluminescent bay. We went on the pontoon boat ($30 person). You have to see it to believe it. When you are in the water and you lift your hand it is like thousands of tiny stars. Only thing with the boat is that they book about 30 people. We lucked out and a tour group didn't show so we had only 9 people. We ate dinner at Duffy's in the town of Esperanza. No frills-great fish tacos- 3 for $10. Many of the restuarants get crowded. Everyone we meet was nice and helpful. we especially liked seeing all the wild horses. We stayed on the island for 3 days, then went back to Fajardo then to san juan. 
