<Author>KBWR
<Content>Could go again... My husband and I just got back from a great trip to Vieques (will post more info in the forums for vieques...)re: the hotel.we went into this not expecting a whole lot, based on other reviews. There were some things we loved and some we didn't1. Our ocean room, which we upgraded to (for $50/night) when we got there was a great big beautiful room. We could see the ocean, after we looked past the pool.2. all the employees were very very very nice.3. the big pretty tub unfortunately only fills with very brown water... a pipe issue, but I get the sense it's not a new issue.4. there are signs to be sure to chain and deadbolt your room, but the chain and deadbolt had both been broken off. I called the front desk and they said, oh, yeah, but the door locks behind you, so you should be fine . and we were fine. :)5. The little thing we can't figure out: apx. 22 people arrived on Sat morning (starting w/ screaming kids at 7:15 am.) They were still there at 10pm when we returned. They rented a room below us, where they had 8 12-packs of coors light that they would go to retrieve - with very loud chattering/ cheering starting around 9am. If we didn't deal with jackhammers on a daily basis we might have been a tiny bit more tolerant, but we came to Vieques for quiet. Ultimately, we had to change rooms, to a non-ocean view room, for the final night, because we knew we couldn't deal with it (especially in the morning!)Yes - it's a one time event - but what concerned me is that the front desk, when we called in the am and then arond 10 pm (to see if the party was still going on) can we come home?, (it was going on - though they said it wasn't)....they claimed to be completely oblivious to the situation. Perhaps because our room (608) is directly at the pool... and the front desk so so far away from the pool, they never knew it.at various times in the evening, before returning and once we returned - we mentioned things like the beer. They all said, oh you should report that, they aren't allowed to do that...Here's the thing - what about the people working at the swim up bar? What about all those people? Certainly they would be making more money if these folks had their drinks versus the ones they brought... so why did it go on and on? without anyone noticing or stopping it? The whole thing seemed really odd and I just don't understand why they decided to let people continue throwing beer tops in bushes and screaming... We were gone for the day, but if we had been stuck there without a car, it would have been very frustrating. I have no problem with people having a good time, honestly, but I really didn't get the sense that everyone was even staying at the hotel.They offered to send security. We took them up on it once, in the early am, but it wasn't efficient. All at the pool went back to the screaming about 20 minutes later.All that being said, the hotel was fine. The spa facilities were nice enough for a shower on our last day... friendly staff. They charge $50 for a late check out, but we just gave the front desk our things and spent our last day swimming in some amazing waves right at the martineau beach. we actually think we would prefer the inn at the blue horizon if we were to go back, (more peaceful, closer to the beaches) but in the same breath - Martineau is probably better if you have kids, the beach was fun on our last day (though waves were way too strong for kids) - and the only place where you can sip a pina colada while you sit on the beach, as the rest of the beaches are undeveloped (thankfully!)one last thing.. we had a very nice taxi driver that they use at martineau...FYI - he is always significantly earlier than you want him to be...this is nice and a little frustrating - he'll wait, but only if he is in the mood to - otherwise, you are just leaving earlier than you want... no biggie, just an FYI! having a little trouble posting photos, but will try! 
