<Content>For the money, you don't get much. My friend and I had a room at Martineau for 4 nights. The girls at the front desk were very cold and unwelcoming. You get the impression their guarding a fortress or something.We figured since it was such a highly rated facility they'd have a hotel shuttle from the airport, since it's right down the street. NOPE! That's ok - the taxi was only $3. Fine.There were no wash clothes in our room so we asked to have some delivered to our room. It took them about 3 hours.The room we stayed in was lovely, but there was some weird lime or some sort of white substance on the floor... We had a lovely view of the pool and the ocean so that was a definite plus.We ate at the hotel restaurant the first night. There wasn't much selection, but the food we had was SPECTACULAR!!! Dessert - not so good... Their idea of creme brule is a coffee cup of custard with a CHARCOAL top. The taste was ok, but the consistency felt like Cream of Wheat.For the amount of money you pay, you really don't get anything but attitude.ADDED NOTE:DO NOT rent from Acevedo Car Rental. They gave us a dilapidated Suzuki Vitara that had no roof, the windows didn't roll up. There was a nest of mosquitoes in the back seat. And it sounded like the jeep was going to snap in half every time you hit a bump (which, on Vieques streets, is A LOT). We arranged with the owner of the rental service, to leave the jeep at the port, since we had to leave first thing in the morning. He said he'd pick it up - no problem. I called his cell phone to confirm he got the jeep and that everything was ok. He would not answer my calls and tried to charge my credit card a bunch of money with no explanation.Still trying to resolve this. 
